This paper discusses a new method for assigning credit to search operators in evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of optimization and machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on adaptive methods, which suggests a potential fit with the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical interpretation of credit assignment, which could also align with the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method, which could also fit under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
